<div id="review_182966426" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/182966426" />
    <a title="Lisabet Sarai" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3438671-lisabet-sarai"><img alt="Lisabet Sarai" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442454421p2/3438671.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/182966426?book_show_action=true">Jul 07, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lisabet Sarai" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lisabet Sarai" href="/user/show/3438671-lisabet-sarai">Lisabet Sarai</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9780553575491" href="/book/show/359390.Holy_Fire">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer182966426" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6980525572056459967">A thoughtful consideration of what the world might be like when technology can &quot;cure&quot; aging. I read this perhaps fifteen years ago, but I was recently reminded of it by a news article claiming that we&apos;ll all be living to at least 150, in good health, within a decade or two. The book considers what it might be like to be an old person in a young body - not as great as it sounds. Now that I&apos;m older, I think I can appreciate the conflicts even more than when I read this. </span>
  <span id="freeText6980525572056459967" style="display:none">A thoughtful consideration of what the world might be like when technology can "cure" aging. I read this perhaps fifteen years ago, but I was recently reminded of it by a news article claiming that we'll all be living to at least 150, in good health, within a decade or two. The book considers what it might be like to be an old person in a young body - not as great as it sounds. Now that I'm older, I think I can appreciate the conflicts even more than when I read this. </span>
  <a data-text-id="6980525572056459967" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


